abstract: Ms. Tennant said she found her footing after discovering writers whose anti-realist qualities dovetailed with her love of myth, magic and dream.
snippet: Ms. Tennant said she found her footing after discovering writers whose anti-realist qualities dovetailed with her love of myth, magic and dream.
lead_paragraph: Emma Tennant, who blended fantasy, science fiction and social satire in dozens of novels that explored the borderland between daylight and dreams, anatomized contemporary Britain and updated the works of Jane Austen and other classic writers in sequels that often had a feminist twist, died on Jan. 21 in London. She was 79.

abstract: Journalists were in a state of shock a day after Sean Spicer, the press secretary, employed a combative tone and false statements in his first appearance on the White House podium.
snippet: Journalists were in a state of shock a day after Sean Spicer, the press secretary, employed a combative tone and false statements in his first appearance on the White House podium.
lead_paragraph: For wary Washington journalists, it seemed only a matter of time before Donald J. Trump’s presidency would lead to a high-tension standoff between his administration and the news media.

snippet: Tom Price, the health and human services pick, Scott Pruitt, chosen to lead the E.P.A., and others faced aggressive questioning at hearings but avoided major stumbles.
lead_paragraph: Democrats complained mightily about their questions being limited, but the Republicans, who hold the majority, get to set the rules. Four of President-elect Donald J. Trump’s cabinet choices faced aggressive questions, but avoided any major stumbles. Here are 10 highlights:

abstract: Donald J. Trump, and eventually his children, repeatedly sought business in Russia as far back as 1987, in a variety of ventures. But none got off the ground.
snippet: Donald J. Trump, and eventually his children, repeatedly sought business in Russia as far back as 1987, in a variety of ventures. But none got off the ground.
lead_paragraph: It was 2005, and Felix Sater, a Russian immigrant, was back in Moscow pursuing an ambitious plan to build a Trump tower on the site of an old pencil factory along the Moscow River that would offer hotel rooms, condominiums and commercial office space.

abstract: Mr. Lilly, a fly fisherman, outfitter and retailer, came to embrace catch and release in order to protect the fish population in his native Montana.
snippet: Mr. Lilly, a fly fisherman, outfitter and retailer, came to embrace catch and release in order to protect the fish population in his native Montana.
lead_paragraph: Bud Lilly, a fly fisherman and conservationist whose fervent advocacy of catch and release inspired people to call him “a trout’s best friend,” died on Jan. 4 in Bozeman, Mont. He was 91.

abstract: “If you try to go tweet-to-tweet with him, more often than not you’re not going to succeed,” a candidate to lead the Democratic National Committee said at a forum.
snippet: “If you try to go tweet-to-tweet with him, more often than not you’re not going to succeed,” a candidate to lead the Democratic National Committee said at a forum.
lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — As the candidates for chairman of the Democratic National Committee gathered here for a forum on Saturday, they wrestled with a vexing question: how to confront the asymmetrical political warfare of President-elect Donald J. Trump.
